Choupo was conceived and architected by Vítor Geraldes.

Substantial parts of the initial implementation, guides, and tutorial corpus
were produced with assistance from Anthropic Claude Code using Claude
Opus/Fable models.

This is an AI-assisted work, not an autonomous AI work. The scientific and
engineering choices, architecture, prompts, acceptance/rejection, corrections,
licensing, trademark strategy, and release responsibility are human decisions.
The acknowledgement is deliberately explicit because pretending either "a
human typed every line" or "an AI authored the project" would be false.

This is the human-readable roll of everyone who has contributed code, cases,
tests, models, executable examples, or project maintenance to Choupo. The
authoritative, fine-grained record of contribution authorship is the git
history.

Project lead and architect
  Vítor Geraldes

Scientific curation, review, and editorial responsibility
  Vítor Geraldes
  Pedro Mendes

AI-assisted implementation
  Anthropic Claude Code / Claude Opus and Fable models
  Used as software-generation tools; not treated as human authors or
  copyright holders.

Code, case, test, and model contributors
